oakcurric:unit-3021
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: basic tactics to overcome opponents in donor sports"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-basic-tactics-to-overcome-opponents-in-donor-sports" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores tactics to overcome opponents with a focus on keeping
  possession of a ball either in hand or at your feet. Pupils will learn how to move on and
  off the ball to create space, to create options and to outwit others in ‘donor’ sports and
  scenarios that can be applied to many sports."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have explored basic principles of attack and defence
  and experimented with tactics and power plays. They will unpick why creating space is
  essential for success in invasion games and how to achieve this as a team with deception,
  creativity and the use of set plays. The importance of good positioning and a strong stance
  is explored both when shooting and defending. The unit will take an overarching look at the
  basic tactics required to outwit opponents without focussing on a specific sport or activity.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3021-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3021-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3021-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3021-4 ;
  curric:id "3021"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.672631Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-engagement-and-enjoyment .

oakcurric:unit-3049
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Striking and fielding: officiating your own small sided cricket games"@en ;
  curric:slug "striking-and-fielding-officiating-your-own-small-sided-cricket-games" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop consistency, timing and fluency in the execution of
  batting, bowling and fielding skills as well as providing pupils with the opportunity to
  demonstrate integrity through officiating their own games."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have explored techniques for batting and overarm
  bowling in cricket whilst also improving their effectiveness fielding to deny runs.
  Statistical analysis will help with decision making as they transition to small-sided rather
  than pairs games. Later in striking and fielding games pupils will be challenged to adapt and
  transfer skills to softball whilst learning a new set of rules, techniques and tactics.
  Leadership skills will continue to be developed in a number of upcoming units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3049-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3049-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3049-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3049-4 ;
  curric:id "3049"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.779567Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-3047
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Dance: the challenge"@en ;
  curric:slug "dance-the-challenge" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit utilises a pure approach that allows action-space-dynamics-relationships
  to be combined with fluency, accuracy and detail with each lesson being driven by a
  different stimuli to challenge creativity and problem solving drawing upon prior learning
  and preparing pupils for KS4."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit offers scope for pupils to draw upon prior learning and combine
  the performative, choreographic and stylistic features to produce a range of effects and be
  able to accurately identify the strengths and weaknesses in their own work and that of
  others. Pupils will be able to make recommendations for improvement. The abstract nature of
  the work encourages pupils to air original ideas building confidence and skills in
  performing, choreographing and appreciating dance and how it allies or responds to other
  artforms to deepen their understanding for further study and/or later life.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3047-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3047-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3047-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3047-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3047-5 ;
  curric:id "3047"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.785009Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-cultural-and-ethical-awareness .

oakcurric:unit-3038
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Outdoor adventurous activities: physical and intellectual challenges"@en ;
  curric:slug "outdoor-adventurous-activities-physical-and-intellectual-challenges" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores pupils' ability to respond effectively to problems and physical
  challenges, both individually and in cooperation with others. Developing awareness of
  others and ability to work in teams is essential to success in life and in this unit."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have developed basic skills to operate as a team but
  this unit challenges pupils to apply them in unique scenarios that require problem solving
  and creative thinking. Later in outdoor adventurous activities pupils will get the
  opportunity to engage in activities beyond the school walls, which will further develop their
  teamwork and leadership skills.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3038-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3038-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3038-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3038-4 ;
  curric:id "3038"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.009863Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-3048
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Net and wall games: overcome opponents in tennis challenges"@en ;
  curric:slug "net-and-wall-games-overcome-opponents-in-tennis-challenges" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will provide pupils with the opportunity to transfer their hand-eye
  coordination and racket skills to tennis through a range of court games that develop
  skills further and introduce tennis specific rules, scoring and tactics. Pupils will be
  challenged to play by the rules."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have shown commitment to developing their badminton
  skills in games of singles and doubles. They will have had experience officiating and
  analysing performance which can now be applied to tennis. Later in net and wall games they
  will learn to apply key principles in volleyball and table tennis.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3048-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3048-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3048-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3048-4 ;
  curric:id "3048"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.087659Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

