  amount of time (under 2 minutes)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301724Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22730-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Feel: resilience is demonstrated by working at high intensity on every exercise."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22730-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: team working skills are developed by sharing feedback to support others and
  listening to advice from peers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301733Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22784-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: a low and agile body position is assumed to make a well timed and safe
  tackle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301737Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22784-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: tracking the attacker’s hips helps maintain balance and stay in line for an
  effective tackle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22784-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: getting back onside after a tackle allows your team to stay organised and
  avoid giving away a penalty."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301745Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22784-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: confidence to make a safe tackle with either shoulder comes from repetition at
  increasing intensity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22784-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: working in a flat line in defence enables a team to cover space and support
  each other when making tackles."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22841-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: when the ball is hit to the boundary, it often requires a second fielder to
  help relay the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302289Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22841-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: considering the abilities of the chasing fielder will lead to taking up a
  good position when relaying the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302293Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22841-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: taking on a leadership role requires a commitment to serve others in favour
  of personal gains."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302297Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22841-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: happiness comes when your team is performing well, especially when your
  leadership/contribution aids success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302301Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22841-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: social integrity involves acting in ways that are just and fair, and
  contributing positively to the community."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302305Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22765-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: different situations require a range of throwing and catching techniques."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302309Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22765-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: fielders backing up a teammate's throw avoids losing runs through
  overthrowing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302312Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22765-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: overarm throws are used for longer distances or more powerful throws, but
  underarm can be more accurate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302316Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22765-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: perseverance is required when throwing for targets and becoming more
  accurate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302322Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22765-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: getting opposition players out in cricket requires increased team
  collaboration when working under pressure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302326Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22790-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: a punt kick involves striking the ball with the instep to ensure accuracy."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302330Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22790-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: tracking the ball early and cushioning the ball ensures it can be passed
  quickly after catching."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302334Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22790-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: accurate kicking allows you to move the ball, create scoring opportunities
  and switch play quickly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302338Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22790-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: utilising a variety of foot and hand eye coordination requires confidence in
  those skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302342Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22790-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: supporting and encouraging your teammates when they make mistakes is
  important when playing competitive games."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302348Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22825-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: successful transitions and formations include judging patterns, orders,
  spacing and dynamics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302501Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22825-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: combining two different elements requires competency in both."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302505Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22825-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Think: making choreographic decisions involves evaluating possible choices."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302509Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22825-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Feel: sharing opinions and ideas honestly demonstrates integrity."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302513Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22825-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: accurate placement in formations requires cooperation from everyone
  involved."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302519Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22778-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: the skills that you can perform with the greatest level of fluency, control
  and consistency are your most refined."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302523Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22778-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: applying reasoning to judgements about your performance helps to ensure
  accurate conclusions are made."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302527Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22778-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: reflecting on performance in a wide range of activities provides a sense of
  achievement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302531Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22778-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: sharing opinions about the strengths of others offers an alternative view
  to make informed decisions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302535Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22844-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: performing at our very best when running requires applying the correct
  technique consistently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302541Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22844-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: tweaking technique before training to achieve a goal gives you a better
  chance of making progress."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302545Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22844-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: understanding a realistic level of improvement helps you set a SMART goal
  that is achievable and relevant to you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302549Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22844-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: reflecting on what you could improve helps you feel more in control of your
  development."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302553Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22844-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: giving focused feedback on technique and discussing your SMART goal helps
  you support each other’s progress."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.302557Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22744-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: net shots require very little backswing and instead meet the shuttle as close
  to the net as possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.305360Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22744-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: smashes are hit with downward force and a flick of the wrist."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.305364Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22744-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Think: disguising which shot you are playing can wrong foot your opponent."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.305370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22744-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Feel: inspiration comes from problem solving and experimentation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.305374Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22744-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: sympathetic feeds that are challenging but possible are the best way to
  support each other to develop."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.305380Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22767-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: bowling a ball requires a side on stance with a straight arm which follows
  through to point at the target."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.306246Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22767-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: releasing the ball at the highest point of the bowling action will contribute
  to ensuring it is a legal ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.306250Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22767-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: bowling the ball to the correct areas of the pitch will ensure it is legal
  and not a no ball or wide."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.306254Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22767-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: focusing on learning a complex skill can be a great distractor from everyday
  stress."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.306258Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22767-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: providing feedback to a partner helps them understand their performance of
  a complex skill and correct errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.306262Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22748-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: sweeping both hands across the body and following through in the direction of
  the pass increases accuracy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.311835Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22748-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: making eye contact with the receiving player before passing avoids handling
  mistakes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.311839Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22748-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: you are not allowed to pass the ball to a teammate who is closer to the
  oppositions try line than you are."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.311843Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22748-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: innovative passing techniques include offloading in contact and running
  different lines in attack."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.311847Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22748-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: with practice you can almost sense where teammates will be but eye contact
  before passing is preferable."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.311851Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22800-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: lifting onto your toes between shots speeds up reactions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312811Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22800-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: hitting the shuttle away from the better opponent requires consistent accuracy
  and control."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312816Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22800-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: playing defensively and waiting for your opponent to make a mistake is an
  effective strategy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312820Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22800-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Feel: persevering despite the challenges shows resolve."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312824Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22800-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: working effectively as a team is achieved by supporting, motivating and
  encouraging each other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312828Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22749-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: supporting the ball carrier is best achieved with runs at pace from deep."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22749-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: side-steps help when dodging round and wrong footing defenders but need to be
  done at pace."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22749-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: ensuring the ball keeps moving up the field either via running or passing
  prevents stalemate situations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312892Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22749-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: reading, reacting and selling dummies to the opposition are creative ways to
  break the gain line."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312896Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22749-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: repeated practice with the same individuals enables accelerating to
  correctly time a support run to improve"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312900Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22783-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: keeping your head to the side and leading with your shoulder makes tackling
  safer and reduces risk of injury."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312915Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22783-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: wrapping your arms fully around an opponent will help control the tackle and
  bring them down effectively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312919Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22783-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: making contact above the shoulders is illegal and puts players at serious
  risk of injury."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22783-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: confidence comes from practising correct technique and trusting your body in
  each tackle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312927Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22783-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: adjusting the intensity applied to a tackle helps build confidence in less
  experienced/smaller players."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22713-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: land the ball close to the target, releasing at the lowest point of the
  underarm swing with a slight wrist flick."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22713-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: ensuring an activity is accessible to all participants is fundamental to
  creating an inclusive competition."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312939Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22713-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: creating an inclusive game where all players are active builds a culture of
  inclusion and belonging."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312943Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22713-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: seeking the voices of all participants in creating a competition makes
  everyone feel included and valued."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.312949Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22695-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: good jumping mechanics include landing with feet parallel to ensure the jump
  distance is maximised."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22695-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: performing an effective long jump requires a one foot take-off followed by
  stretching ‘for the trapeze’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317648Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22695-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: ensuring you perform the 3 phases of the long jump correctly will ensure you
  perform a legal jump."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317654Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22695-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: being determined to perform at your best will help to achieve personal best
  results."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317658Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22695-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: helping others by giving them instant performance feedback will enable them
  to understand how to improve."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317662Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22746-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: playing to the back by hitting deep forehand and backhand shots, helps build
  winning opportunities."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22746-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: when officiating, it is important to make loud, clear calls of the score or
  whether the shuttle lands in or out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22746-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: if your team's score is even then you serve from the right, if it is odd, you
  serve from the left."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317744Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22746-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: achieving a personal best performance isn't always about winning the
  match."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22746-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: ethics in sport are moral principles that guide us to play fairly with
  respect, integrity and good etiquette."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22761-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: rapid hip and knee flexion enables you to duck and avoid capture."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317777Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22761-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: controlled slow and steady movements will help us stay in time with
  others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317781Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22761-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: adjusting plans in response to the opposition's actions improves our chance
  of success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317787Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22761-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: stretching yourself beyond your comfort zone helps develop confidence in
  situations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317791Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22761-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: we must sometimes take the lesser roles to secure overall success by the
  team."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317795Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22838-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: clapping, running over to someone or giving a high 5 after they perform well,
  reflects physical appreciation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317802Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22838-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: applying the rules fairly requires taking an impartial stance, even when you
  want to win."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317806Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22838-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: your own good performance and contribution to your team performance can bring
  joy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317810Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22838-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: taking it in turns to experience all the playing positions enriches the
  experience for all."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.317814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22694-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: running over different distances or times requires different styles and paces
  to achieve your best performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318735Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22694-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: starting an extended run at a pace which is sustainable will avoid creating an
  oxygen debt and tiring."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318739Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22694-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: calculating how fast you can run and for how long will help you to select the
  right pace."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318743Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22694-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: listening to your body during extended running and striving to keep going
  demonstrates self-motivation"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318750Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22694-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: contributing to a team effort and encouraging team mates can foster a sense
  of belonging."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318754Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22781-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: selecting and applying the most relevant skills in relation to the activity
  increases the chances of success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22781-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: being clear on the rules and conventions of an event and communicating that
  to others ensures a fair competition."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318762Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22781-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: all forms of contributions to the event play a vital role in its success and
  foster a sense of achievement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318768Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22781-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: accepting victory and defeat graciously helps to maintain a positive
  environment for all performers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318773Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22818-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: participating in activities with maximum effort allows for a fun review of
  leadership."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318777Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22818-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: constantly evolving as a leader and working on areas for improvement requires
  reflection."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318781Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22818-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: growing in confidence while developing leadership requires listening to our
  strengths and areas of development."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318785Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22818-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: trust in ourselves and others is developed through openness and
  reflection."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318789Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22678-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: moving quickly into a space to attack requires running with fast feet."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318815Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22678-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: different attacking options have specific positional spaces and
  responsibilities."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22678-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: to almost unconsciously move into a free space to receive a pass requires
  anticipation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318823Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22678-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: when you are free for the ball it is important to look for and communicate
  this with your teammates."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318827Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22762-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: coordination is essential for maintaining control and allowing smooth
  transitions between movements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318845Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22762-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: balance is required to transfer weight forward onto the other foot in time
  with others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318849Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22762-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: everyone needs to be clear on the task and focused to achieve it
  together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318853Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22762-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: valuing others shapes how we interact with people and builds meaningful
  positive relationships."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318857Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22762-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: coordinating movements to be in time becomes tougher as group size
  increases."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.318861Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22797-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: contact is made above and out in front, with body weight shifting forwards for
  overhead shots."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321384Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22797-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: quick reactions to lunge and flick the wrist on contact with a shuttle help
  deflect a defensive shot back."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321388Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22797-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: a flick of the wrist turns a clear into a smash if the shuttle is above and
  in front."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321392Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22797-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: focusing on performance rather than outcome goals helps maintain
  motivation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321398Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22797-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: supporting others to practise tasks that are just hard enough aids
  progress."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321402Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22799-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: effectively covering the space on the court involves moving back if your
  partner moves to the net."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321406Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22799-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: knowing a shuttle in the middle of the court should be played by whoever can
  hit a forehand is smart tactics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321410Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22799-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: being dedicated to working with your partner to achieve the best possible
  outcome shows commitment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321414Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22799-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Connect: being positive helps avoid deterioration in performance"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321418Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22735-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: when preparing to jump or turn, stand tall with feet together, swing arms back
  and always land with bent knees."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321422Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22735-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: the higher you jump, the more time you have to complete the shape or rotation
  and land correctly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321426Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22735-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: explaining the teaching points of jumps/turns to others helps to improve your
  own knowledge and performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321430Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22735-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: controlling the release from the jump/turn and land requires repeated practice
  which also builds confidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321434Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22735-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: supportive feedback to peers on strengths and areas for improvement in jump
  technique requires sensitivity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.321437Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22852-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: increasing overload using FITT pushes the body beyond its current level."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325452Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22852-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: combining stretches and muscular contractions is required to perform
  proprioceptive neuromuscular facilitation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325456Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22852-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: reflecting on the effectiveness of adjustments using the FITT principle
  ensures appropriate progression."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325460Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22852-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: having courage to trust a partner enables a wider range of performance
  enhancing stretches."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325466Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22852-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: working in pairs with clear communication and trust helps pupils to stretch
  safely and effectively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325470Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22851-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: increasing overload on the body will ensure it continues to adapt and make
  progress."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325497Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22851-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: planning for suitable increase in overload using the FITT principle reduces
  risk of injury or burn out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325500Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22851-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: challenging yourself to work harder than you did previously gives you a sense
  of satisfaction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325504Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22851-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: discussing how to safely increase training with others helps share ideas
  and encourages mutual support."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22773-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: maintaining a forward and relaxed alternate arm action helps maintain speed
  and balance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325724Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22773-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: increasing stride length and/or stride frequency towards the end of a run can
  improve time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22773-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: being able to maintain a \"race pace\" for the full distance of a race
  without fatigue will maximise performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22773-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Feel: running alongside others can help to regulate emotions during training."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325736Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22773-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: running with others in pairs or small groups can help with motivation over
  longer distances."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325740Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22640-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: precise movements in the right direction are achieved by always facing
  forwards."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325759Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22640-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: negotiation involves critical thinking skills to reach a mutually beneficial
  agreement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325763Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22640-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Think: elimination involves considering and then rejecting possible choices."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325766Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22640-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Feel: being part of a team to solve a problem stimulates feelings of self-worth."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325773Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22640-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: adaptability is essential when working as part of a team to problem
  solve."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325777Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22842-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: the reverse sweep is performed by rotating the bat and sweeping the bat from
  in front of leg side to the off side."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325821Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22842-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: selecting the reverse sweep requires quick decisions based on the nature of
  the bowling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325825Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22842-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: considering how others must be feeling and experiencing emotions can help to
  suitably respond and support them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325831Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22842-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: successfully playing an advanced shot such as reverse sweep in competitive
  situations should make you proud."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325836Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22842-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: supporting others to manage their emotions requires sensitivity and good
  perceptions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.325840Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22835-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: reducing the speed on second serves, increases the probability of getting it
  in."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327427Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22835-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: understanding that if the score has been tied at 30-all, you need to win 2
  consecutive points to win the game."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327431Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22835-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: knowing how to take control of the game when you are serving, increases the
  chances you will win the point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327435Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22835-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: controlling your emotions and managing risk in shot selection is required to
  maintain effective performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327439Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22835-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: working together in pairs, over time, builds strong bonds through respect
  and empathy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327445Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22831-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: gentle strokes with a short backswing and follow through improves
  accuracy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22831-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: the ready position is assumed quickly between shots to make it quicker to
  respond to the next shot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327453Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22831-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: knowing control is more important than power but topspin helps keep the ball
  down in the court increases success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327457Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22831-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: challenging yourself to be consistent and avoid mistakes requires
  self-discipline."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327461Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22831-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Connect: cooperation with others is required to maintain a consistent rally."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327465Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22752-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: a safe tackle is made by hitting the ball carrier low, with your head to the
  side of their body and wrapping arms."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327503Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22752-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: keeping arms wrapped until the ball carrier is secured on the ground, before
  releasing, prevents a missed tackle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22752-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: if your head is in front of the ball carrier there is a high risk of
  injury."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327512Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22752-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: playing with different people can increase experience at responding to how
  attackers try to evade space."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327516Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22752-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: adjusting the intensity applied to a tackle helps build confidence in less
  experienced/smaller players."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.327522Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22843-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: driving hard against the ground in the first strides helps you accelerate
  quickly at the start of a sprint."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.330611Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22843-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: settling into a relaxed rhythm early helps you to stay controlled and pace
  your 800m effectively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.330615Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22843-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: assessing how your body responds to different levels of intensity enables you
  to make informed decisions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.330619Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22843-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: reflecting on your own abilities and limitations can provide a focus for
  self-improvement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.330623Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22843-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: helping others by timing their benchmarking supports accuracy and builds
  mutual respect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.330627Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22668-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: focusing on control, body language and tension can enhance the aesthetics of
