oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22644-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: encouraging our peers when completing maximal exertion tasks shows good
  collaboration."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395592Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22656-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: clear arm signals are given when refereeing to ensure players can see the
  decision."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395596Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22656-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: players have 4 seconds to restart play from kick-ins, free kicks, goal
  clearances and corner kicks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395600Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22656-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: determination and focus are required regardless of role (player or official)
  to perform at your best."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395604Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22656-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: it is essential to avoid bias by always treating players fairly rather than
  giving favouritism to your friends."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395610Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22704-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: extending the arm back, while looking forward, provides a stable target for
  the incoming runner to aim for."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395614Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22704-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: the receiver should accelerate to a sprint by the time the incoming runner is
  ready to exchange the baton."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395618Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22704-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: the receiver must begin to run at a precise moment to ensure the changeover
  is performed at high speed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22704-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: striving to apply our very best effort shows self-motivation and supports our
  team to achieve success in relays."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395628Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22704-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: communication from the incoming runner to the receiver is vital to ensure
  the changeover is a success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395632Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22848-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: a tall upright posture with a strong core and relaxed shoulders is required to
  perform efficiently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397838Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22848-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: optimising your stride length enables you to maintain good posture and avoid
  overextending your legs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397842Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22848-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: maintaining good posture at all times helps to reduce strain on
  joints/muscles and leads to fewer injuries."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397853Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22848-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: refining the technique of running helps to build self-esteem and reduces
  anxiety of being watched."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397858Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22848-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: providing positive feedback about technique shows a respect that can build
  self-esteem when performing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397862Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22850-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: clear replication of test protocol is essential to ensure it is a reliable and
  valid result."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22850-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: emotional and physical responses to testing should be more positive in
  relation to the start of the unit testing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397869Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22850-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: evaluating progress in relation to your previous performance can improve
  self-esteem and motivation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397873Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22850-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: recognising progress in others, no matter how small, can motivate them to
  continue with their programme."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397877Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22829-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: stillness requires the precise use of balance, strength and control."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22829-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: an aesthetic dance will include both physical and expressive skills."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397885Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22829-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: deciding when and how to apply stillness involves evaluating the effect from
  the audience’s perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397889Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22829-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Feel: useful feedback is delivered with honesty and integrity."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397893Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22829-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: making adjustments to choreography requires all performers to cooperate
  fully."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397896Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22734-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: a full circuit training session is completed with good technique and full
  range of movement at the joints."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397900Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22734-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: progressive overload is incorporated into each station by increasing the reps
  or decreasing the rest interval."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397904Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22734-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: adaptations occur as a result of regular training, however if training stops,
  reversibility will occur."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22734-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: to keep working when progressive overload has been applied to the circuit
  requires increased resilience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397914Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22734-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: being an effective gym buddy involves supportive feedback on technique and
  setting targets."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397918Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22819-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: taking three steps with the ball in hand enables the creation of space to pass
  or shoot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397922Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22819-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: dribbling low and close using fingertips helps to stay in control and quickly
  change direction or speed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397927Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22819-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: players can dribble the ball but can only hold it for a maximum of three
  seconds before passing or shooting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22819-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: adapting to rules that allow three steps whilst carrying the ball takes time
  to reset the muscle memory."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22819-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Connect: supporting less confident classmates shows kindness."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397939Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22759-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Move: contracting our core muscles stabilises the body and improves balance."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399355Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22759-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Think: taking your time to avoid mistakes often ends up faster in the long run."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399359Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22759-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: avoiding the temptation to give up in the face of difficult challenges
  requires determination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399363Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22759-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: working as a team requires clear communication and shared
  responsibility."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399367Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22661-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: good springboard technique requires a controlled run up and correct foot
  placement on the springboard."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399428Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22661-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: taking off from the springboard involves pushing upwards and extending the
  arms overhead to assist with height."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399432Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22661-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: understanding how good technique using a springboard can generate flight will
  help you perform controlled jumps."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399436Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22661-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: continuing to try even when apprehensive about using a springboard will
  develop your self-confidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22661-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: completing group challenges using a springboard requires excellent
  collaboration and communication skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399444Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22806-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: linking movements together seamlessly requires spatial awareness, momentum and
  good body control."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401635Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22806-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: good decision making skills are required to choose the best movements to link
  together to create a sequence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401639Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22806-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: completing challenging sequences helps you believe in your ability and develop
  confidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401643Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22806-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: working together and supporting each other developing sequences involves
  communication and respect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401647Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22715-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: use your arms and legs to slide or pivot on the floor to reach the ball
  quickly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22715-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: to set, gently push the ball upwards using your fingers, without carrying or
  holding the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22715-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: sending the ball to parts of the court that are free from opponents will
  increase the chances of winning rallies."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22715-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: regulating emotions during competition can make it a more positive experience
  for you and your opponents."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401663Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22715-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: being gracious shows respect, builds positive relationships and promotes a
  healthy, supportive environment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401668Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22659-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: maintaining equal weight distribution between each partner ensures stability
  and balance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401673Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22659-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: holding weight on hands requires an engaged core to keep the body aligned and
  prevent strains."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401677Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22659-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: holding your own/your partner's weight on different body parts is important
  when performing paired balances."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22659-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: repeated practice with a partner builds up confidence to try more complex
  balances."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401687Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22659-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: counterbalancing with a partner requires trust and clear communication to
  maintain counter tension."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401691Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22667-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: a quality routine requires control, consistent flow, accurate timing and
  excellent movements from start to finish."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402563Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22667-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: deciding which movements to perform as a group requires analysing various
  options."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402567Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22667-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: if a mistake is made, continue to keep the routine flowing and show poise to
  minimise further deductions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402573Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22667-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: demonstrating confidence when performing helps execute skills making it more
  visually pleasing for the audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402578Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22667-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: motivating and setting targets for classmates can help as they seek to
  complete their best performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402582Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22687-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: throwing involves standing sideways on, swinging the throwing arm from behind
  the body to the front to release."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402721Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22687-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: catching requires you meet the ball with your hands, cup/grasp the ball and
  cushion it into the waist"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402727Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22687-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Think: power comes from an overarm throw and accuracy with underarm throws."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402735Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22687-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: helping teammates to improve their catching and throwing skills shows
  excellent integrity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402740Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22687-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: to be compassionate to teammates receiving the ball, adjust throwing style
  and speed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402743Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22688-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: hitting action requires a smooth backswing, head over the ball and a follow
  through keeping control of the bat."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403291Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22688-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: it is most effective to hit the ball away from fielders, into vacant/empty
  spaces."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403295Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22688-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: changing the angle of the bat on connection enables hitting the ball in
  different directions to avoid fielders."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403299Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22688-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: when the bat connects cleanly with the ball, it provides a sense of
  achievement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403303Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22688-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: batting requires patience as you take it in turns to bat, allowing others
  to hit the ball before and after you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403307Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22840-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: wicket keepers need to position themselves crouched low and ready to move
  quickly and catch."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22840-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: wicket keeping is a high pressure role in which you must focus fully on every
  ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403459Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22840-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: deep breathing or counting to 10 are methods of controlling emotions and
  keeping at your best under pressure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22840-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: joy and sadness are to be expected when winning or losing in a game, but
  understand it does not define you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22840-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: when others have won or lost, it is important to show empathy to all
  involved."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

