oakcurric:keyword-pressure-in-sport
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "pressure (in sport)"@en ;
  schema:description """mental and physical stress athletes feel from high expectations or wanting
  to perform well"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.405053Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Misconceptions
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:misconception-roll-ball-height
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You can roll the ball from any height."@en ;
  curric:correction """It is more accurate to roll the ball from a lower position which is achievied
  by bending your knees."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086110Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-focus-pushing-ground-maximum-force
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Focus on pushing off from the ground with maximum force for height or distance
  and prioritising speed of execution."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The most critical skill for precision, confidence and long term athletic
  health is the ability to efficiently absorb and redirect force upon landing. A powerful
  jump with a weak or uncontrolled landing risks injury."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086153Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-common-mistake-pupils-make-using
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A common mistake pupils make is using a 'bowling' style of throw in which the
  throwing arm remains straight throughout the action."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask pupils to think about pulling the javelin through, with the elbow leading
  first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086165Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-once-motif-created-stay-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Once a motif is created it has to stay the same and can't be adapted."@en ;
  curric:correction "You can always adapt a motif by changing the actions, space or dynamics."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086190Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-gymnasts-need-good-flexibility
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Only gymnasts need good flexibility."@en ;
  curric:correction """Flexibility is important for performance in any activity/sport. Essentially,
  it is important for every day health and wellbeing, especially to avoid lower back pain
  and poor posture."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086260Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-throwing-something-force-make-accurate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Throwing something with more force will make it more accurate."@en ;
  curric:correction """Increased force usually reduces accuracy unless the technique is correct
  (stance, grip, arm swing and follow through)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086308Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-need-either-logical-thinking-creative
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You need either logical thinking or creative thinking in isolation."@en ;
  curric:correction """When you use both logical and creative thinking together, you can plan
  clearly, adjust your approach and find the best solution, even when a task is challenging."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086330Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-racing-heart-feeling-breathlessness-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A racing heart and feeling of breathlessness means you need to slow down."@en ;
  curric:correction """You need to build up gradually and pace yourself at the start of a run, but
  feeling out of breath and a racing heart rate is normal during sub-maximal exercise."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086360Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-struggling-coordination-means-clumsy-careless
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Struggling with coordination means you are clumsy, careless or simply not
  trying."""@en ;
  curric:correction """During adolescence, rapid growth spurts cause a temporary mismatch as limbs
  are longer than the brain thinks they are, which causes a calibration error. Consequently,
  it is essential to keep practising fine and gross motor skills as you grow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086391Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-honesty-required-time-poeple-watching
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Honesty is required at all time, not just when poeple are watching."@en ;
  curric:correction """Honesty is always important because it shows who you really are. Being honest
  builds trust, helps you feel proud of your choices and means that you do the right thing,
  even when no one is watching."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086745Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-perfect-balance-means-moving
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Perfect balance means not moving at all."@en ;
  curric:correction """Balance is actually a constant series of tiny corrections. Your brain and
  muscles are in a non-stop conversation, making micro-adjustments to keep your centre of
  gravity over your base. This happens in static and dynamic balances."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087041Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dribbling-ball-your-head-look
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When dribbling the ball, your head should look at it."@en ;
  curric:correction """When dribbling, your head should look up to develop kinaesthetic awareness
  and maintain ball control, without bumping into anything in the working area/environment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087065Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-training-maximal-effort-push-past
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Training must be at maximal effort to push past the pain."@en ;
  curric:correction """The focus should be on vigorous activity. Listen to your body and work at a
  high intensity, but one that is dicated by your current fitness levels and the sort of
  exercise you are used to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087071Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-need-use-safe-lifting-technique
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You only need to use safe lifting technique if the item is heavy."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whenever we are bending down to something pick up, we still must bend from
  the knees and protect our back to prevent possible straining from leaning over."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-need-go-gym-build-muscle
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You need to go to a gym to build muscle strength and endurance."@en ;
  curric:correction """Body weight exercises, that require little or no equipment, can be performed
  in a safe space in your own home and can be incredibly effective at building muscular
  strength, endurance and general fitness."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087499Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dance-routine-cannot-repeat-motifs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A dance routine cannot repeat any motifs within it."@en ;
  curric:correction """A dance routine can use repeated phrases of movement, for example, when a
  chorus comes back on within the song."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087578Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-best-hit-ball-little-power
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "It is best to hit a ball with very little power."@en ;
  curric:correction """You need to use some power to hit the ball to allow the ball to bounce,
  especially if it is a soft ball or some rolled up socks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088413Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-play-target-games-another-person
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You can only play target games with another person."@en ;
  curric:correction "Target games can be played with other people and by yourself."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089231Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-perform-motif-same-speed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You always perform a motif at the same speed."@en ;
  curric:correction "Often you adapt your motif to the speed of the music you are dancing to."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089470Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-applying-dynamics-fast-actions-strong
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When applying dynamics, fast actions are always strong."@en ;
  curric:correction """We often tend to combine fast actions with strength and slow actions with
  softness but this isn't always the case. Slow and strong could suggest great effort
  against resistence, and fast and light actions communicate fluidity and ease."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093797Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-performing-pulling-counterbalance-pupils-hold
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When performing a 'pulling' counterbalance, pupils should hold hands."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are many ways to perform 'pulling' counterbalances other than using
  hands, but if doing so, pupils should clasp one another's wrists to make a more secure
  connection."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093802Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-shooter-allowed-d
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think the shooter is allowed in the D to score (like netball)."@en ;
  curric:correction """The only person allowed in the D is the goalkeeper, shooters have to shoot
  from outside the D, otherwise the goal doesn't count."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094009Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-player-taking-throw-needs-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Only the player taking the throw-off needs to be in their own half."@en ;
  curric:correction """All players must be in their own half before the throw-off is taken, not just
  the thrower."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094014Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-soloing-ball-pupils-dont-flick
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When soloing the ball, pupils don't flick their toe upwards causing the ball
  to travel in front of them. When passing, pupils throw the ball, forgetting the correct
  open or closed hand passing action."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When the foot impacts the ball, flick your toes up so the ball travels back
  into the hands. Pupils should spend a lot of time repeating their hand passing skills to
  avoid throwing the ball when under pressure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094028Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-add-content-their-sequence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils add more content to their sequence, they can lose flow with the
  sequence looking unpolished. Pupils show limited variety in their locomotive elements."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Practise the sequence slowly at first, focusing on smooth transitions between
  movements and balances. Encourage pupils to be creative and add variety to their
  locomotive movements throughout the sequence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094071Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-circuit-involve-exercises
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think a circuit has to involve exercises in a circle."@en ;
  curric:correction """A circuit is a series of exercises done a specific order but does not have to
  be set up like a circle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094584Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-hip-hop-dance-style
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Hip Hop is a dance style"@en ;
  curric:correction """Hip Hop is a generic term for a number of dance styles that are heavily
  influenced by street culture (DJing, graffiti, rapping). There are a large number of
  subdivisions which vary according to time and place of origin."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094590Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-performers-participate-competitive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils believe only performers participate in competitive events."@en ;
  curric:correction """Competitions depend on various roles to run safely and efficiently.
  Performers can only participate if officials and organisers set up the event correctly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095264Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-winning-metric-success-losing-bad
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Winning is the only metric of success and losing is always bad."@en ;
  curric:correction """You can make improvements to your own/your team's performance in many
  different ways, regardless of the outcome of a competition."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-teaching-offside-rule-pupils-struggle
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When teaching the offside rule, pupils often struggle with understanding a
  player is offside when the ball is passed to them not when they receive it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use cues to show the moment the ball was passed. For example, you could ask
  the pupils to freeze just as the ball is passed to determine whether they are offside or
  not."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095278Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-quick-get-emotional-challenged
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be quick to get over emotional when challenged with being the
  official, leading to inaccurate, unfair or even biased decisions being made."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils must learn to regulate their emotions when acting as the official to
  ensure competition is fair."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096176Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-good-leaders-born
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think good leaders are born like that."@en ;
  curric:correction """Effective leadership is developed through experience and learning from
  mistakes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096182Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-take-multiple
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often think they need to take multiple touches before passing
  the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to make quick decisions using one or two touch passes, and
  encourage pupils to scan before receiving the ball so they know where to pass to next."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-short-steps-run
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils use short steps and run through as they hit the shuttle which leaves
  them out of position for the next shot."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Using long lunges and recovering back to the middle of the court quickly
  between each shot reduces the space and options available to your opposition."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-losing-track-time-becoming-distracted
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Losing track of time or becoming distracted by the freedom of navigating
  without the direct supervision of a teacher."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus in on school values and responsibility to retain the privilege of
  independence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096220Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-look-their-feet-lack
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often look down at their feet and lack core stability when balancing,
  which shifts their centre of gravity so they are off balance."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should focus on looking slightly forward on a stable point at eye
  level and learn how to engage their core when balancing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096721Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-constantly-change-directions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think you can constantly change directions when chasing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that in Kho Kho, chasers cannot change direction freely. They
  must run around a turning pole to change direction. Turning mid-court is a foul."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096729Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-conflict-negative-avoided
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think conflict is negative and should always be avoided."@en ;
  curric:correction """In reality, resolving conflict is an important lifeskill that can also be the
  catalyst for creativity and innovation. It can challenge assumptions but does need to be
  managed constructively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096735Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-steps-learnt-performed-set-order
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The steps learnt have to be performed in a set order."@en ;
  curric:correction """In the Lindy Hop, the dancers' personal style and flair was highly prized so
  they would find new and inventive ways of arranging and performing the key actions seen it
  this style."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096760Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-spatial-awareness-rotating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle with spatial awareness when rotating their body. Poor posture
  and body alignment means pupils lose control and balance when rotating."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to practise 90 degree rotations initially and then build up
  to larger rotations. Encourage pupils to use visual cues so they look at a particular spot
  when rotating. Encourage pupils to engage their core to maintain good posture."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-gs-static-position
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A GS is a static position."@en ;
  curric:correction """The GS can move out of the goal circle to create space for the GA to drive in
  and receive the ball. A shooter position requires dynamic movements such as power to jump
  for a rebound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097234Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-batting-dont-need
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that when they are not batting, they don't need to pay
  attention to what is happening on the field."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Being a good team member requires us to encourage our teammates and be aware
  of what is happening in the game, even when our turn to bat has not finished or even
  started yet."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098042Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-their-release-point
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle with their release point when bowling underarm which results
  in an illegal bowling action. Pupils are too slow to throw from backstop to first base
  when trying to run the batter out."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should focus on a smooth pendulum action when bowling to ensure that
  the ball is bowled between knee and head height and to the side of the batter. When
  backstop has the ball, focus on a flat, hard throw to first base to run the batter out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098058Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-leading-giving-instructions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think leading is just about giving instructions."@en ;
  curric:correction """A ledaer also requires active listening and the time and confidence to
  provide feedback on what has been completed well and how things can be improved."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098422Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-seek-easiest-opportunity-guarantee
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils seek the easiest opportunity to guarantee a win."@en ;
  curric:correction """Winning an unfair or unbalanced race/competition is a hollow victory and
  greater satisfaction comes from winning a balanced contest where both individuals/teams
  have a good chance of winning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098439Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-swing-hard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think they need to swing hard at volleys."@en ;
  curric:correction """When approaching the net to volley you already have momentum moving forwards
  into the ball which adds power so a more effective technique is to block and sometimes
  even cushion the pace out of the ball whilst angling it back over the net."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-likely-focus-people-famous
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils are likely to focus on people who are famous."@en ;
  curric:correction """It is entirely possible that pupils are naturally drawn to people who are
  famous, but it is still feasible to identify the qualities and behaviours that have made
  them successful such as hard work, determination or courage."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098652Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-strength-power-important-technique-throwing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Strength and power are more important than technique when throwing a javelin
  far."""@en ;
  curric:correction """While strength and power are both important, too much strength and not enough
  time focusing on technique, can impact the accuracy of the throw. A well executed throw
  will travel further than just force alone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098672Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-focus-power-rather-accuracy
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may often focus on power rather than accuracy when shooting. They may
  also make poor decisions with regards to shooting when under pressure such as facing a
  goalkeeper or a defender."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus on accuracy over power, working on aiming for specific targets. Pupils
  should practise shooting under pressure to help them make good decisions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098857Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-attack-territory-middle-court
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils attack territory down the middle of the court or pitch and it becomes
  crowded."""@en ;
  curric:correction """By using accurate passing and movement of the ball out wide, you draw
  defenders out and create more space to invade. Similarly, by moving the ball back and then
  forward again, you can create more space."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-better-move-ball-one-hand
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """It is better to move with the ball in one hand and score a try with
  one hand."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Despite it perhaps being more comfortable to have the ball in one hand (or
  under the arm) when running, it does not keep the ball as safe and therefore increases the
  risk of dropping the ball and therefore your team losing possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098886Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-take-wrong-foot-performing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often take-off with the wrong foot when performing the thief vault or
  they take-off too close to the obstacle."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Work on take-off in isolation, focusing on taking-off with the outside foot
  and ensuring there is enough space between them and the obstacle to ensure continued flow
  through the vault."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099101Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-effective-leaders-loud
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think all effective leaders are loud and shout to be heard."@en ;
  curric:correction """It is common to hear a leader with a voice which is projected when
  communicating. However, there is so much to effective leadership beyond verbal
  communication, such as, active listening, knowing your team and showing empathy, to name a
  few."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099116Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-tuck-their-head
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often forget to tuck their head when performing forward and backward
  rolls causing a rough landing or strain on their neck."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The chin should be tucked gently into the chest looking at their stomach.
  This will protect the neck and keep the head aligned."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-combining-different-phases
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often struggle with combining the different phases of the triple jump
  in the correct sequence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Build up to the full performance gradually, without an approach to begin with
  and gradually introducing one at walking pace and then jogging pace. Have a partner coach
  the performer to check their coordination and technique to quickly correct errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099127Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-putting-unique-action-pupils-unwittingly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Putting is a unique action and pupils often unwittingly revert to a throwing
  action which can lead to injury. Throwing is against the rules/regukations, thus it is
  also often illegal in competitions"""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage the key technical points of holding the shot against the neck
  throughout the preparation and pushing the shot phases first, alsongide the key point
  about a straight wrist and extending elbow following behind at all times."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099165Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-bowling-same-length
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that bowling should always be at the same length to be
  consistent. The phrase 'good length' might be part of the confusion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should understand that as long as it is a legal ball, the length can
  vary. This is a good way to outwit the batter as different lengths create different
  challenges and keeps them guessing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099351Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-chest-pass-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think the chest pass is only used for shorter distances."@en ;
  curric:correction """The chest pass is a very versatile technique that can be used for short and
  longer distances. It works well as a technique to pass when aiming for the space a
  teammate is moving into."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099376Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-quick-focus-their-feedback
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils are often quick to focus their feedback on something which went wrong
  or needs improvement, without considering the impact of identifying what is also being
  performed well."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils can use methods such as the 'feedback sandwich' which encourages them
  to think about identifying positive aspects of performance as well as areas for
  improvement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101148Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-move-slowly-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think you should only move slowly with the ball so you don't lose
  posession."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Moving fast with the ball can create more opportunities to beat defenders,
  create space and keep the attacking momentum strong."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101160Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-common-mistake-triple-jump-athlete
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A common mistake in the triple jump is the athlete collapses the middle 'step
  phase' rather than getting equal height and distance from every phase."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasis on all phases of the jump should be practised, especially the step
  phase, with height and efficiency. All phases of the triple jump should contribute to an
  equal proportion of distance e.g. 2m x2m x2m"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102126Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-trust-others-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to trust others to have their back."@en ;
  curric:correction """Trust is a two-way process and something that needs to be earned and then not
  taken advantage of."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102131Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-swing-hitting-drop-shots
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils swing when hitting drop shots and net shots."@en ;
  curric:correction """By reducing your backswing and almost eliminating your follow through, you
  will be able to perform more successful drop shots and net shots that trickle just over
  the net and put your opponent under more pressure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102399Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-stand-behind-ball-hit
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often stand behind the ball and hit up at it rather than moving their
  body to get into a better position."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You need to move your feet quickly to get to the side of the ball to use a
  smooth U shaped swing on the forehand or backhand and hit through the ball towards the
  net."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102410Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-circuit-training-solely
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that circuit training is solely to improve components of fitness
  but not for developing skilled sports performance."""@en ;
  curric:correction """While circuit training is great for improving components of fitness, it can
  also be designed to develop sport-specific skills. For example, in basketball, a circuit
  can include dribbling, shooting and passing stations, alongside fitness exercises."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102416Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-goal-target-end
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think a goal or a target it the end product or outcome to be
  achieved."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A goal can be based on outcome, however it can also be a goal set about the
  performance or process of doing something. For example, building a 3-2-1 pyramid in the
  quickest time compared to building the 3-2-1 pyramid without dropping any objects."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102421Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-understand-relationship-rest-workouts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not understand the relationship between rest and workouts,
  believing that more training, equals more progress."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Help pupils to understand the requirement for sufficient rest and recovery
  time if the body is to make adaptations and improve."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102427Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-big-swing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think they need a big swing and to serve overarm."@en ;
  curric:correction """When we watch pro tennis or other racket sports it looks like you need a huge
  swing and lots of power but when you are starting out you will get more success with a
  slow and controlled swing. Pickleball (like badminton) starts with an underarm serve."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102438Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-route-one-utilising-width-depth
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Route one - not utilising width or depth and just crowding the ball down the
  middle of the pitch/court."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When attacking, it is important to use the full width of the pitch/court to
  draw defenders out and create space for a scoring opportunity. It is also sometimes
  necessary to move the ball back, before moving forward again, if the space is too crowded."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-movement-important-movement
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think the only movement that is important is the movement with the
  ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Movement off the ball is just as important, it helps create space and
  supports the player in possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102496Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-repeating-same-drills
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that repeating the same drills every session is the best
  way to improve."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Even performing the best drills or exercise will become boring after time.
  Therefore variation is required in a training programme, otherwise it will become boring
  and the athlete will lose interest."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102516Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-unable-adjust-their-team
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils are unable to adjust their team tactics based on the situation."@en ;
  curric:correction """Changing the way you play as a team to include formation, tactics and roles
  of different players can have a huge impact on the game and a shift in momentum that
  disrupts your opposition."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102760Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-wait-until-their-opponent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils wait until their opponent hits the shuttle before starting to initiate
  movement to retrieve it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If you wait until you know where the shuttle is going before starting to
  move, you will often be too late to get to it. Instead, pre-load your legs with a split
  step to trigger an explosive lunge to reach the shuttle faster."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103226Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-anaerobic-exercise-useful-improving-your
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Anaerobic exercise is only useful for improving your ability to run fast."@en ;
  curric:correction """Anaerobic training can also build muscular strength, power, endurance and
  improve body composition. All of these can benefit your performance in many different
  sports not just running."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103588Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-making-tackle-need
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget that after making a tackle, they need to get back onside in a
  straight line."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Response: after a tackle, the whole defensive line need to be back onside 10m
  from the play of the ball. If you are not moving as a flat line, you leave gaps for
  attackers to break through."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103593Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-fielder-chasing-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that if they are not the fielder chasing a ball, they are
  not needed, even though the chasing fielder cannot throw the full distance to the wickets."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should understand that fielders need to work together and if they
  think the fielder will struggle to throw the distance, they should support by positioning
  themselves to relay the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103772Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-throwing-target-pupils-think-hitting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When throwing at a target, pupils will often think only of hitting the target
  and not the consequences of missing it - which often leads to losing more runs through
  overthrowing it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils understand the need to back up their teammate as they throw, and the
  need for the thrower to check that someone is backing up before throwing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-kicks-lack-necessary-power-accuracy
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Kicks may lack the necessary power or accuracy, or they might often miss their
  target. High catches can be intimidating and pupils may mistime their jump."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus on good technique before increasing distance or adding movements to
  kicks. When performing a high catch, track the ball early and use the jumping technique to
  meet the ball when it is at its highest point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103786Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-performing-group-formation-unison
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When performing in a group formation, this should always be in unison."@en ;
  curric:correction """Unison can be highly effective in clear formations as this also communicates
  unity and power, but other choreographic relationships such as canon, mirroring or contact
  work also add interest and are visually exciting to watch."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103842Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-throwing-events-same-technique
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All throwing events have the same technique."@en ;
  curric:correction """While there is a common core technique across all throwing events, each event
  has a unique set of technical elements that range from the grip, stance, release and
  recovery phases."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103850Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-setting-realistic-goal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often struggle with setting a realistic goal for themselves, often have
  plans that are too ambitious for the time available or opportunity to train towards it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should be aware that progress over several weeks can be marginal and
  that fitness gains take time and consistency. They can use the resources provided to help
  set realistic goals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103856Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hold-their-index-finger
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils hold their index finger up towards the shaft of the racket to try to
  get more control."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Letting your index finger point up the back of the grip feels like it is
  helping with control, but break this habit fast to prevent this technique from limiting
  your progress to the full range of shots that are possible with a shake hands grip."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105020Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-common-error-made-beginning-learn
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The most common error made when beginning to learn how to bowl in cricket is
  that pupils throw the ball with the elbow bending in the action which is not allowed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to understand that the action requires a straight arm and this
  should be emphasised throughout the lesson. It is perhaps a unique throwing action which
  takes time to adjust to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105307Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dont-need-practice-passing-because
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """I don't need to practice passing because I can already catch well and have
  good technique."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Passing isn’t just about mechanics, it’s also about teamwork. Practicing with
  different teammates helps improve subtle communication, like eye contact and timing, and
  allows you to understand how others prefer to receive the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107110Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-instinctively-want-work-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils instinctively want to work with their best friend and/or the 'best'
  partner."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When playing matches, it's fulfilling when a competition is balanced and
  offers an equal chance of winning. To achieve this, pair up pupils based on current
  performance levels or agree a number of starting points to give to one of the
  people/teams."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107393Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-evading-space-solely-ball-carrier
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Evading space is solely about the ball carrier getting past the defender."@en ;
  curric:correction """In reality, a supporting runner's positioning often determines whether an
  attacker breaks the gain line. A well-timed support line can draw defenders, create
  passing opportunities, or make a dummy pass more effective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107421Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-tackling-harder-makes-effective
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Tackling harder always makes it more effective."@en ;
  curric:correction """Controlled technique, not force, makes a tackle successful and reduces the
  chance of injury or penalties."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107434Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-target-games-played-against-people
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Target games must be played against people of similar ability or previous
  experience for it to be a fair competition."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Conditions can be put on specific players in target games to balance the
  competition, regardles of their ability or previous experience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-perfroming-long-jump-many-pupils
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When perfroming the long jump, many pupils take a long step into the pit which
  means they land with one foot in front of the other which reduces the distance they
  achieve."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should be taught to land with feet parallel by bringing the take-off
  foot through and in front of them so that no distance is lost and they achieve a maximal
  score."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-blame-other-lose-focus
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils blame each other and lose focus rather than remaining positive and
  regrouping."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that the balanced teams mean everyone should have an equal
  chance of winning. Hence it is the pair who gel the best and work hard to win as many
  points as possible across all their matches that will win."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108793Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-players-desperate-get-oppositions-treasure
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """All players are desperate to get the opposition's treasure so they have a high
  risk of getting caught and neglecting the protection of their own treasure."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Let pupils do it however they like first but then give time to regroup and
  plan a smarter team strategy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108798Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-celebrating-others-achievements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not always recognise that celebrating others' achievements is an
  important part of their own development and contribution to the team."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils that part of the game is to show respect and to respecfully
  physically appreciate it when someone performs well."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-start-long-distance-running
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils start long distance running too fast through a mixture of excitement,
  copying each other and overestimating the pace they can maintain."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise the need to calculate and find a suitable pace and consider how
  sustainable a fast pace is going to be."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109090Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-poor-sporting-behaviour-related-people
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Poor sporting behaviour is only related to people who spectate or support the
  events."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Everyone involved in the competition is responsible for how they behave and
  showing good sporting behaviour. This includes supporters, performers and officials.
  Everyone's role is to ensure the event remains safe, fair and enjoyable for all."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109097Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-self-assessment-similar
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think self-assessment is similar to being assessed in something."@en ;
  curric:correction """Self-assessment is an opportunity to reflect and does not count towards any
  assessment. It is positive. Leaders are able to grow from self-assessments as they
  recognise strengths, but more importantly, identify keys areas of improvement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109103Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-opposite-team-scoring
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that the opposite team to the scoring team take the following
  center pass."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The center pass is alternated throughout the game regardless of which team
  scores."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-rushing-complete-task-therforemfailing-listen
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Rushing to complete the task and therforemfailing to listen to, or consider,
  all group members."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Together Everyone Achieves More, it is essential to work as a TEAM and ensure
  everyone is valued."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109180Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hit-shots-similar-technique
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils hit all shots with a similar technique and avoid high risk, powerful
  smashes to avoid losing points."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Practising smash shots is necessary in order to take your game to the next
  level."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109981Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-dont-adapt-their-court
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils don't adapt their court position based on where their partner is and
  where the shuttle has been hit."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Work together to cover the court. If your partner is at the front of the
  court then it is important to step back to cover the back of the court. However, it is
  typically easier to assume side-by-side positioning and cover half the court each."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110001Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-dominate-discussion-less-confident
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may dominate the discussion with less confident pupils unwilling
  to take their turn at leading. Pupils might take too long explaining and not leave enough
  time to practise."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Select the numbers carefully so that pupil 1 and 2 are more confident and can
  model teaching first, giving less confident pupils time to get used to this process.
  Stress the importance of practise time and keep explanations concise."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110008Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pnf-confused-partner-simply-helping
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """PNF can sometimes be confused as a partner simply helping to deepen the
  stretch by pushing a bit further."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The method of contracting the muscle activates the nervous system which helps
  improve flexibility more effectively than static stretching alone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111284Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-massively-misjudge-much-incremental
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often massively misjudge how much incremental overload can be achieved
  week on week."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that small incremental increases in overload using the FITT principle
  will bring about results safely."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111304Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-get-faster-running-middle-distance
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """To get faster at running middle distance you always have to train at race
  pace."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Improvements in speed and fitness for middle distance running can also come
  from running easy efforts. This builds aerobic fitness and gives the individual a strong
  base where over time the same effort will be maintained but at a faster pace."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111368Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-letting-vocal-pupils-make-decisions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Letting the most vocal pupils make all the decisions as they have the
  answers."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The loudest people don't always have the best ideas. If you are a dominant
  character it is especially important to invest time in learning how and when to be quiet,
  to listen or to invite others to contribute."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111379Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-dont-consider-emotions-other
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils don't consider the emotions of other people involved in a game
  which can lead to unsavoury comments after mistakes or poor play."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to consider the emotions of others and how they might be
  able to positively influence the emotions of others through words and actions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111396Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-point-equally-important-tennis
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Every point is equally important in tennis."@en ;
  curric:correction """Break point and other points to the advantage side are far more important to
  avoid losing a game on your own serve or winning/losing a game respectively. In the 2019
  Wimbledon final, Federer won 14 more points than Djokovic, but lost the match."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111858Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-play-full-court
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils rush to play full court from the baseline before they have the racket
  skills to direct the ball accurately and keep a rally going."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Tennis can be a frustrating game with a lot of fetching mis-hit balls. It is
  best to start slow and build your confidence with racket familiarisation and close touch
  control before building in more power to your shots."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupil-think-go-tackle-legs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupil think that if they go in to tackle at the legs they will get kicked in
  the face."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If you tackle low, with your head to the side and wrap their legs with your
  arms, they’ll go down safely and you won’t get kicked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111887Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-benchmarking-times-represent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might believe that benchmarking times represent their fixed ability and
  that their times won’t change."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to understand that benchmarking is a snapshot in time - a
  starting point that effort and hard work can improve (growth mindset)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113172Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-their-feedback-dont
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils rush their feedback and don't give detailed advice to enable pupils to
  make improvements. Pupils may rush to refine their routines without carefully considering
  how they can make improvements."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide numerous examples of high quality feedback throughout to highlight
  your expectations. Ensure that pupils take care over the details to improve their routine."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113178Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-performing-group-routines-means-members
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Performing group routines often means some members of the group may struggle
  with the choreography and therefore feel self-conscious and demotivated."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Stress to each group the importance of adapting choreography to suit the
  needs of everyone in the group. For example, some pupils could perform backward rolls
  whilst others perform a more basic roll. Or everyone may change the skill they perform."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113187Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-performing-unison-students-slightly-ahead
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When performing in unison, some students may be slightly ahead or behind
  affecting overall synchronisation. If pupils don't move at the correct intervals in canon,
  the sequence looks uncoordinated."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use a clear count-in or rhythm (e.g. counting beats out loud or clapping) and
  practise slowly before increasing speed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113205Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-go-offside-footwork
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think when they go offside or do footwork they have to stand out of
  play as this is a penalty pass."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Both of these infringements do not include another player so a free pass is
  awarded. If a player obstructs or contacts an oppositing player a penalty pass is then
  awarded."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113211Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-sides-stick-like
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils use both sides of the stick like they see in ice-hockey."@en ;
  curric:correction """In field hockey you are only allowed to use the flat side of the stick. If
  the ball touches the other side or your foot it is a foul."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113217Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-hip-hop-culture-focuses-disrespecting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Hip Hop culture focuses on 'disrespecting' your opponent and mocking them."@en ;
  curric:correction """As in all competitive settings, the performers are trying to succeed and
  employ a variety of strategies to do so, but this also includes congratulating others on
  their successes and supporting those who are developing their skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113778Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-many-pupils-move-their-feet
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Many pupils do not move their feet in response to the pitch of a ball, instead
  keeping their feet in the same place throughout. This leads to awkward and ineffective
  swings at the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Using tees slows down the thought process so that footwork can be learned
  before facing a moving ball. Almost every shot requires some foot movement and the stance
  should allow for this by being on balls of feet and with knees slightly bent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-tackling-raider-individually
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that tackling a raider individually is the only option."@en ;
  curric:correction """In Kabaddi, Raiders have 30 seconds to make the raid and get back across the
  half way line. As a result, if the defense hold up the raider until their time runs out,
  it is an unsuccessful raid and the raider doesn't score."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113980Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-punctuality-merely-turning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think punctuality is merely about turning up to lessons on time."@en ;
  curric:correction """Punctuality is linked to arrival time, but is also about completing tasks on
  time and being respectful for the time of others. This is achieved by being organised,
  fulfilling the task and being dependable."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-accepting-first-action-pupil-offers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Not accepting the first action that a pupil offers is likely to put
  them off."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Challenging pupils to generate more than one response, or to find ways to
  refine their actions, before making their final selection, enables pupils to develop their
  creativity and understanding of choreographic and performance skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115179Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-way-defend-mark
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think the only way to defend is to mark 1 player on the
  opposite team."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Sometimes moving as a unit, where you shift together, can prevent any of the
  attackers from making a break and getting the ball up the court."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115207Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-big-swing-volleys
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils use a big swing for volleys and consequently regularly miss the ball or
  hit it out."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When playing close to the net, you don't need to apply much swing and instead
  should use the power already in the ball, combined with a step into the shot, to apply
  power with more of a short punching action to block the ball back."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115213Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-team-still-successful-long-its
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A team will still be successful as long as some of its members contribute and
  work hard."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Everyone should be given the opportunity to use their voice and have a role
  to ensure success. Every pupil needs to be encouraged to share their ideas and listen to
  others in each learning cycle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115219Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-emotional-intelligence-simply
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think emotional intelligence is simply about being nice or positive and
  is a fixed trait."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emotional intelligence is recognising, expressing and managing emotions. It
  can be developed and improved with practice and feedback."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-lack-confidence-make-decisions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils lack the confidence to make decisions, often worrying what their peers
  might say if they don't agree with a decision."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide pupils with reassurance that it is acceptable to make mistakes and
  ensure everyone in the group is respectful of decisions made by officials."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-confident-enthusiastic-want
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """There may be pupils who feel confident and enthusiastic and want to take over
  all officiating and not allow others to do so."""@en ;
  curric:correction """All pupils should take some role in officiating. Assign roles such as
  scorecard keeper and person in charge of reading the aims and rules at each event."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116523Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-throw-shot-shot-put
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You throw a shot in the shot put."@en ;
  curric:correction """The shot put does not require any rotation around a joint. It is pushed from
  under the chin and touching the neck. A throw action will likely lead to injury due to the
  weight of the shot. However, \"throw\" is standard terminology for this event."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116551Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-making-loop-passes-effective-attacking
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Making loop passes are effective in attacking situations."@en ;
  curric:correction """Such passes are easy to intercept as they are easy to track and often don't
  go very far."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116593Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-defending-netball-mainly-role-your
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Defending in netball is mainly a role when your opponent has the ball."@en ;
  curric:correction """Defending occurs in all positions and each player needs to track their
  opponent to try to deny them the opportunity to receive a pass."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116610Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-commit-zone-defence-others
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils commit to zone defence but others get distracted into chasing the
  ball, therefore moving out of position."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is essential that all team members follow the same defensive strategy of
  player-to-player or zonal marking to avoid leaving big gaps."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116615Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-wait-until-defender-close
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils wait until a defender is too close before trying to make a pass and
  consequently lose possession often."""@en ;
  curric:correction """By getting control of the ball quickly, looking up to find teammates in space
  and passing before a defender gets too close you can keep possession better."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116627Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-evaluate-others-performances-overlook
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils evaluate each others performances, they overlook the important
  details such as performing with control, extension, flow and accurate timing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make sure pupils are using the worksheet to help them evaluate the sequences
  so that they focus on the fundamentals that make a sequence high quality."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117568Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-choreography-leading-frustration
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may struggle with the choreography, leading to frustration and
  disengagement."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Differentiate within the choreography so that pupils have choices over the
  skills they perform. If you would like all pupils to perform the same skill, make sure
  this skill is accessible for all pupils."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117585Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-call-their-score-first
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils call their score first and get confused which side they should serve
  from."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You should always call the serving player's/team's score first. If their
  score is even, then they serve from the right, whereas if their score is odd, they serve
  from the left."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117591Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-power-sprinting-comes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that all the power in sprinting comes from the legs and not
  use their arms enough when performing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Power in sprinting is created by a combination of powerful legs and arms
  working simultaneously, hence why sprinters often have muscular arms as well as legs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118044Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-attacker-move-soon-their-teammate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "An attacker should move as as soon as their teammate catches the ball."@en ;
  curric:correction """A feint is an effective way to create space as we wait for the ball handler
  to present the ball ready to make the pass, rather than moving too early and the defender
  being able to catch up with you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-opt-perform-simple-movements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils always opt to perform the most simple movements. Pupils may not like
  performing in front of others."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give pupils time to develop their movement ideas and be creative. Share
  creative ideas to improve the quality of movements. Encourage pupils to present in pairs
  to build up their confidence in performing to one another."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-lack-cushioning-hand-foot-keep
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Lack of cushioning with hand or foot to keep close touch control and eyes
  always down to look at the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """By using kinaesthetic awareness (touch) and peripheral vision you can control
  the ball better with a light touch and keep your eyes up to look for space, teammates and
  defenders."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118837Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-make-pass-stand-still
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils make a pass and stand still, waiting for the next ball. This is a
  common issue, especially in futsal, where quick transitions and movement are key."""@en ;
  curric:correction """After passing, always move to create an option. A great habit is to perform a
  give-and-go, where you pass the ball and immediately make a run to receive it back. This
  keeps the game fluid."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118849Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-learning-scissors-technique-pupils-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When learning the scissors technique, pupils often use an incorrect take-off
  foot, choosing to jump from the foot closest to the bar instead of the foot furthest away."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Allow pupils to practise jumping off their right foot, then their left,
  before performing the full action to establish which they prefer to take off with. Be
  observant during full performances and be ready to suggest a pupil changes approach side."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119408Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-supporting-another-person-far-them
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """If supporting another person you should be as far away from them as
  possible."""@en ;
  curric:correction """To support another person effectively, the performers need to be in close
  proximity with the 'supporter' adopting a wide base and using the large muscle groups to
  power the action."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119416Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-include-their-favourite
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think they should just include their favourite exercises in their own
  circuit."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Exercises should be selected and used to target and imporove specific areas
  of weakness, e.g. certain muscle groups, a components of fitness or a sport specific skill
  you need more practice at."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119422Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-lack-movement-ball-teammates-position
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """There is a lack of movement off the ball or teammates position themselves too
  close to the ball carrier therefore making it easier for the defenders to gain possession."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should always be moving off the ball to drag defenders out of
  positions. Pupils should also spread out and position themselves at different angles and
  distances from the ball carrier."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119498Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-make-slow-decisions-covering
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often make slow decisions when covering each other due to lack of
  confidence. They also panic when they are under pressure in a game situation."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage quick and clear communication using captains and coaches to help
  players make good decisions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119504Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-count-music
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils should 'count' the music."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst some pupils can count music accurately, it can be an additional level
  of challenge for others and divert them from the task in hand. Most pupils will naturally
  'feel' the music and be able to respond to the tempo and rhythm appropriately."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120111Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-performers-look-straight-ahead-project
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Performers should always look straight ahead and project to their
  audience."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In many styles, the connection to the audience is an important part of the
  performance. This can also be achieved by including a change of focus to communicate the
  performer's mood or intention, or to indicate what the audience should be looking at."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120128Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-fear-running-speed-jump
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils fear running at speed to jump on to the springboard or are reluctant to
  jump on to a vault/box top. Pupils have poor technique on the springboard. Pupils fear
  straddling the box."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Build confidence by breaking the skill down. Practise without the box top or
  with a lower box gradually increasing height. Develop good foot positioning on the
  springboard before adding in the box top. Pupils could straddle on to the box first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120135Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-dont-align-their-court
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils don't align their court positioning and often find themselves with one
  player forward and one back."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If one player is at the net and one is back on the baseline, it leaves big
  diagonal gaps through the court so it is essential for both be at net or both be on the
  baseline as much as possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120144Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hold-racket-like-frying
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils hold the racket like a frying pan and squat lower and lower to hit
  overhead clears."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A shake hand grip and sideways stance is required to get power and accuracy
  into shots, but you also need to know when it is necessary to hit underarm rather than
  trying to hit everything above the head."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120150Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-new-games-hindered-preexisting-rules
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """New games are often hindered by preexisting rules and scoring systems which
  remain the basis and stunt creativity."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils must think outside the box and forget about pre-existing activities
  when creating their own games. It is important to instil the confidence to try something
  new even if it doesn't work."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120156Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-letting-vocal-students-take-lead
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Letting the more vocal students take the lead improves team outcomes."@en ;
  curric:correction """Outcomes are better if the voices of the whole group are listened to and
  considered."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120320Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-add-their-non-dominant
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils add their non dominant hand to the bottom of the grip when hitting
  backhands."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is essential that your dominant racket hand is at the bottom of the grip
  and if you add your other hand for extra control or power it must go further up the racket
  shaft."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120332Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-teams-dont-discuss-tactics-properly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Teams don't discuss tactics properly and instead focus on just wanting to play
  a game."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Forming a number of predetermined plans can be an effective way to capitalise
  on set play situations and being aware of which team members are the biggest threat to the
  opposition can leave other players more open."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120338Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-wait-until-baton-starting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils wait until they have the baton before starting to run in a relay."@en ;
  curric:correction """Outgoing runners need to move to the start of the exchange zone and start
  their run sooner to accelerate as they are handed the baton on the move. Practise the
  technique from stationary to running to ensure action is well rehearsed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120344Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-underestimate-overestimate-distance-leading
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will often underestimate or overestimate the distance, leading to
  overshooting the jump or falling too short."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that hitting the edge of the mat is crucial, therefore they should
  gradually increase the distance to find the correct one for them. This will also need to
  be adjusted when they add a run up."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122677Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-fear-falling-clearing-obstacle-lead
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Fear of falling or not clearing the obstacle can lead to hesitation which can
  then affect the flow and overall success of the vault."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Gradual progression and practising on lower obstacles can help build
  confidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-uncomfortable-physical-contact
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils are all uncomfortable with physical contact."@en ;
  curric:correction """Contact must involve respect. Care should be taken to ensure any touch is
  appropriate. Most pupils are sensitive to this and respond appropriately. Teachers can
  guide this by identifying how contact should be made, e.g. touch toe to toe."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122697Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-hit-ball-hard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may try to hit the ball too hard when playing competitively. Pupils may
  be dishonest when scoring their own games in the competitions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise the importance of playing accurate and controlled shots rather than
  focusing on hitting the ball hard. Remind pupils of the importance of respect and playing
  by the rules in competitive situations, and to just focus on trying their best."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123447Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-improving-physical-activity
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that improving at a physical activity requires them to
  perform the event in full repeatedly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Help pupils to understand that training drills which overload the body are
  much more effective when training to achieve a goal, rather than simply repeating the full
  performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dancers-silent-performing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Dancers have to be silent when performing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst this is usually the case, dance often connects with other artforms and
  occasionally dancers may also speak, sing or make sounds through body percussion (e.g.
  clapping or stamping)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123483Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-dribble-their-head-focusing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often dribble with their head down, focusing too much on the ball and
  not on teammates, spaces to move into or defenders within the space."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to develop the habit of looking up regularly to scan the
  area."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123500Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-batting-pair-pupils-poor-communicating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As a batting pair, pupils are often poor at communicating when to run,
  sometimes even oblivious of the need to communicate at all."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils a simple code that they can use and when to use it, to encourage
  more understanding of the need to communicate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123505Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-confused-side-serve
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils get confused about which side to serve from and who serves next."@en ;
  curric:correction """A server keeps serving after winning a point and they alternate sides each
  point —from the right if their score is even and left if it is odd. If the opposition wins
  a rally, they earn a point and the service with the other partner serving next."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-best-way-win
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think the best way to win is to hit ithe ball harder."@en ;
  curric:correction """Sometimes just keeping the ball in and waiting for your opposition to make a
  mistake is the best way to win points, but it is also helpful to disrupt the rhythm by
  varying pace/spin, breaking the angle or using disguise to wrong foot your opposition."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123952Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-play-needs-stopped-referee-single
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Play needs to be stopped by the referee at every single rule break."@en ;
  curric:correction """Not every rule break means the game has to stop. The referee can play
  advantage, keeping the game flowing and more enjoyable. However, dangerous play, like high
  tackles, must be dealt with straight away to keep everyone safe."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123958Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-make-big-touch-dont
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils make a big touch so they don't have close control of the ball. Pupils
  slow down after turning with the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to keep the ball close to the body so they have control at
  all times. Pupils should explode after the turn pushing off with their standing leg."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123983Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-capoeira-use-pre-recorded-music
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "In Capoeira you use pre-recorded music."@en ;
  curric:correction """In Capoeira the music is played live and the tempo and style of the music
  dictates the style of the game that will be played."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123997Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-requirement-keep-checking-location-ensure
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Requirement to keep checking location to ensure on track. Regular stopping and
  time wasting as a result of re-orientating the map."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Thumbing the map means tracing your route as you move along the map to
  represent where you are on the map at any given time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124461Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-playing-part-bigger-team-pupils
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When playing as part of a bigger team, pupils often bunch around the ball and
  do not hold their shape. They can also be more static off the ball thinking that teammates
  will be available for a pass."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Reduce the numbers on each team, assign clear roles or freeze the play
  regularly to demonstrate where players should be. Focus on movement off the ball as soon
  as players have passed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-hiit-experienced-athletes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think HIIT is only for experienced athletes."@en ;
  curric:correction """HIIT can be modified to suit all fitness levels. It can be a valuable and
  quick tool to improve many components of fitness. The intervals can be shorter for
  beginners and the exercises less intense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124472Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-teaching-use-additional-materials
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils are teaching, they do not use the additional materials and
  therefore provide incorrect teaching points or unsuitable adaptations for their group."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils are using the additional materials to support their
  understanding of each skill and make sure they know how to provide adaptations so that
  everyone in the group can achieve success when performing the skill."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124532Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-belief-our-identity-fixed-permanent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A belief that our identity is fixed and permanent."@en ;
  curric:correction """Who we are and how that is expressed can be changed, and is likely to shift
  throughout our life. We can communicate who we are through our expression, how we dress,
  how we speak and by taking part in activities that are important to us."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-forward-rolls-pupils-tuck-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """With forward rolls, pupils may not tuck their chin, leading to discomfort.
  They may struggle to generate enough momentum to complete the roll."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise tucking the chin to protect the neck and practise rocking back and
  forth from a crouched position to develop momentum. Break each roll down into manageable
  steps."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125013Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-player-player-marking
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that when you are player-to -player marking it is only about
  being an individual."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Defenders must communicate, adjust to overloads and support each other. If
  one defender gets beaten, others need to be ready to help. Marking your player is just one
  part of working together to stop the attack."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125035Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-motif-variation-motif-development-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Motif variation and motif development are the same thing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Variation and development are both methods of motif manipulation. However,
  during variation, the action content remains the same but how it is presented can be
  changed. Whereas, development involves significant alteration to the actions themselves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-link-pieces-apparatus-together
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often link pieces of apparatus together e.g. benches attached to a
  table which limits the use of space and options for pathways. Pupils rush to create
  balances that are not of high quality."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to place apparatus in spaces to allow them to explore
  interesting pathways and to be able to use each piece of apparatus in creative ways. Peer
  assessment of balances can encourage refinement and increase quality of pupils work."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-tournaments-focus-solely-outcome-winner
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All tournaments must focus solely on the outcome/winner of competition."@en ;
  curric:correction """In order for all participants to feel included, tournaments can take many
  forms and be adapted so that everyone can enjoy an appropriate level of challenge."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126120Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-failing-remain-goal-side-whilst
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Failing to remain goal side whilst keeping a view on the player and
  the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Failing to remain goal side of your opposition exposes yourself to an easy
  scoring opportunity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126125Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-swing-bat-across-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will swing the bat across their body like a baseball bat which
  increases the chance of missing the ball, edging it or getting out."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should understand that because of the way the ball is bowled in
  cricket, playing with a straight bat is often the most effective way to strike and not
  risk your wicket."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126131Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-argue-decisions-particularly-close
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may argue about decisions, particularly close calls such as run outs.
  This can often lead to the decision going in the favour of the more dominant or boisterous
  pupils."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should experience the umpire role to practise making fair decisions
  and develop empathy, helping them understand not to challenge calls."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126220Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-wrong-hand-leads
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils use the wrong hand which leads to fouls and ineffective tackles, or
  they dive into the tackle, allowing attackers to easily sidestep away."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Always use the nearest hand to flick the ball away. Stay balanced when
  tackling, moving your feet quickly and timing the tackle properly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127395Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-everyones-sprinting-technique-look-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Everyone's sprinting technique should look the same."@en ;
  curric:correction """Everyone will have their own natural style of running. Forcing pupils to be
  too upright for example may be sub optimal for some. Pupils should find their natural
  position which may include a slight lean."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.128036Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-maintain-their-shorter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often believe they can maintain their shorter distance pace over the
  longer distance, without needing to adjust."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Longer distances require more controlled pacing. Running a 1500m at 800m pace
  or a 200m at 100m pace will almost always lead to early fatigue and poor performance.
  Learning to distribute your effort is key to completing longer events effectively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.128226Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-partner-balance-counter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that a partner balance is a counter balance. Pupils may
  struggle with counter balance due to unequal weight distribution. Pupils may struggle to
  trust their partner."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show the difference between a partner balance and a counter balance. Pupils
  practice positions individually and work together to adjust the balance equally.
  Incorporate activities that require working together and communication to build trust."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130429Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-unaware-variety-training-methods
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be unaware of the variety of training methods available to use for
  improving fitness and performance."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Continue to give pupils experiences which demonstrate different methods of
  training and ways to structure sessions, such as interval and plyometric training."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130726Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cant-see-outcome-your-performance
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """If you can't see the outcome of your performance, you are unable to learn how
  to improve."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Receiving feedback from teammates and other pupils about your performance
  will enable you to learn and make progress."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130746Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-rushing-figuring-strategy-consequently-making
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Rushing before figuring out a strategy and consequently making mistakes"@en ;
  curric:correction """Take time to plan your strategy first to avoid losing more time by being sent
  back to the start"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.131630Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-crowding-around-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Crowding around the ball"@en ;
  curric:correction """By taking the ball out into the wide channels on a pitch/court, you draw
  defenders out of their area and create space elsewhere to pass to your own players and
  make an attack on goal."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.131636Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-confidence-constant
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think confidence is constant."@en ;
  curric:correction """Fluctuations in confidence are very normal. It is not a static state and
  often determined by the environment your are in and any previous experience you have of
  that environment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.131650Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-confusion-transferring-route-map-real
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Confusion transferring the route from the map to real life."@en ;
  curric:correction """By orientating the map and holding it facing the same way relative to key
  features/north, you can quickly navigate around and avoid confusion every time you change
  direction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132357Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-believing-hard-work-involves-rushing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Believing that hard work involves rushing to complete the maximum number of
  repetitions but with poor form."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Doing less movements with the correct technique will have a more positive
  impact on fitness than blasting out lots with poor form/range of movement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-recognise-right-movement
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to recognise the right movement to execute different
  strategies, which results in losing possession or missed opportunities."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Break down the games so you can focus on good decision making. Stop game play
  when a poor is decision made to ask pupils to identify and resolve the problem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132397Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-solve-problem-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think to solve a problem has a just one single option."@en ;
  curric:correction """Problem solving is not linear, nor is there only one universal problem
  solving technique. The right approach depends on the nature of the problem in a specific
  context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132402Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-capoeira-based-fighting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Capoeira is based on fighting."@en ;
  curric:correction """Capoeira is based on challenging your opponent, but in a game-like scenario.
  This is why performers are called 'players'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132408Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-hurdles-daunting-many-pupils-fear
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Hurdles is daunting for many pupils who may fear hitting the hurdle, falling
  or getting hurt, which are justifiable concerns. This causes them to do things such as
  stutter their approach or even stop."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Be careful to provide hurdles which are achievable for all abilities and
  gradually allow pupils to build confidence and progress to higher hurdles when ready,
  rather than expect them to hurdle the full height."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-hit-serve-hard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think they have to hit the serve as hard as possible to be
  effective."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Placement, spin and consistency are far more important when learning to
  serve."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-serve-towards-middle-court
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils serve towards the middle of the court which is easy to return."@en ;
  curric:correction """Aiming their serve to force a defensive shot from their opponent is a much
  stronger way to start the point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133882Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-fast-heart-rate-feeling-nausea
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A fast heart rate and feeling of nausea is dangerous and you should stop
  exercising."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This is quite normal and a sign that we are challenging our fitness. It is
  important to get used to the way our body feels when we start to exercise. Seek guidance
  if this concerns you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133894Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-need-feel-hyped
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that they need to feel hyped up or overly energised to
  perform well."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Overexcitement can lead to mistakes, such as, starting too fast or losing
  focus. Controlled breathing and mental rehearsal help you stay calm, focused and perform
  more efficiently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134456Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-get-mat-bar-falls-still
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """If you get off the mat before the bar falls it will still count as a
  successful jump."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If the bar falls then the jump does not count, even if the jumper has left
  the mat. Every attempt should be made to clear the bar rather than rushing the landing and
  clearing the mat quickly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134468Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-make-quick-decisions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle to make quick decisions and perform skills correctly when
  defenders are present and adding pressure."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind players to scan before receiving the ball. Use mini games or time
  limits in tasks so pupils are used to performing under pressure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134473Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-kick-good-kicked-far
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A kick is only good if it is kicked far."@en ;
  curric:correction """Kicking a ball successfully involves accuracy and tactical placement to find
  space, kicking into touch or to allow one of your team to catch and maintain possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134495Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-fake-subtle-performed-fast-enough
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The fake is too subtle and not performed at a fast enough pace. Pupils make
  fake too early so it is easy to read."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use clear and exaggerated movements when faking and shift your weight
  explosively. Wait until the defender is close before performing your faked movement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134754Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-winning-important-thing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that winning is the most important thing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Learning to value a fair competition and choosing to lose in preference to
  cheating to win or only playing opponents you know you can beat, is a much more rewarding
  outlook."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136352Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-its-ok-stop
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that it's ok to stop and stand mid-court."@en ;
  curric:correction """It is essential to return to the middle of the court and split step as your
  opponent hits the ball to load elastic energy in your legs to be able to move quickly.
  Don't get caught standing between the baseline and non-volley line on approach to net."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136371Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-confident-players-shooting-range-failing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Confident players shooting from out of range and failing to pass when would
  have been a better option."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Getting in a strong position with a high probability of scoring if you shoot
  is essential. It is important to pass to a teammate in a better position rather than shoot
  when out of range."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136526Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-jumping-apparatus-pupils-rush-jump
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When jumping from apparatus, pupils may rush the jump and not be balanced
  before they take off. Pupils may land with stiff knees or poor body position."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Always check balance and engage the core before jumping. Ensure a solid
  stance before jumping. Pupils should bend their knees to absorb impact on landing and make
  sure their weight is centered over their feet."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136705Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-lack-confidence-officiating-fear
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may lack confidence when officiating and fear making incorrect
  decisions. They may also struggle with peer pressure and be tempted to change their
  decisions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to make clear, firm decisions and remind them that mistakes
  are part of learning. Teach referees to stand by their decisions and use short, clear
  explanations. Also ensure the players are respectful of those decisions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137670Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-passing-distance-much
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often find passing over distance much harder and try to kick the ball
  too hard. Often pupils are too close together so no one is in a wide position to aim for."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to slowly increase the distance at which they pass so they
  maintain control and accuracy. Pupils should be encouraged to adopt wide positions when
  attacking, stretching defenders to create space."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137677Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-forgetting-align-north-compass-north
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Forgetting to align north on the compass with north on the map before
  navigating"""@en ;
  curric:correction """Hold the compass next to the arrow representing magnetic north on the map and
  rotate your body until the arrow on the map and the arrow on the compass line up with
  north, then keep the map facing that way even when you change direction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137685Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-win-quickest-race-complete-tasks
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "To win you must be the quickest and race to complete tasks"@en ;
  curric:correction """If we rush communication, we will not properly understand which will lead to
  mistakes. Even if we finish first, it will be irrelevant if the task is completed
  incorrectly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137691Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-poor-foot-placement-wall-performing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Poor foot placement on the wall when performing tic tacs and wall runs can
  result in poor technique and a weak push off. Poor control on landing is also a common
  issue with Tic Tacs and Wall Runs."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use visual cues (e.g. chalk marks or splat spots/cones) on the wall to show
  the ideal contact point. Also use markers to indicate where to land and teach pupils to
  land quietly and stick their landing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138074Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-fundamental-movement-skills-fms-needed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "fundamental movement skills (FMS) are only needed at primary school."@en ;
  curric:correction """FMS underpin good movement in any activity and in wider life, so it is
  essential that we continue to practise and hone these basic movements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138080Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-miss-tackle-give
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think if they miss a tackle, they should just give up."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to show determination to chase back and continue to pressure the
  attack, even if they miss a tackle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138085Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-aerobic-training-relevant
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think aerobic training is only relevant for endurance athletes like
  long distance runners."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Aerobic training is useful for any athletes that play sports that last longer
  than 20 minutes, e.g. rugby, netball football, hockey."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138094Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-adaptable-leader-forced
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think being adaptable as a leader is when there is a forced change."@en ;
  curric:correction """Adaptability for an effective leader is when it is always happening and the
  leader is responding to how the needs of the group are being met and if the environment is
  working or not."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138103Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-acceptable-copy-work-others-dance
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "It is acceptable to copy the work of others in dance."@en ;
  curric:correction """Copying the work of others and passing it off as your own is known as
  plagiarism. However, identifying features that are common to a dance style and applying it
  to your choreography is different, but should remain respectful to the original source."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-trial-people-judged-see-makes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A trial is where people are judged to see who makes the cut and who
  doesn't."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A trial is an opportunity for everyone to show what they can do and also
  learn where they could focus on as priority areas for improvement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138117Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-thinking-heart-rate-breathing-rate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Thinking the heart rate and breathing rate are zero when at rest."@en ;
  curric:correction """Our body needs the energy from the oxygen we breathe in order to maintain
  basic living functions, hence why our heart rate is always raised above 0."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-lack-confidence-officiate-game
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may lack the confidence to officiate a game and may struggle to take
  control of the game. They may be biased towards certain teams depending on who they are
  friends with."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Create a safe, encouraging environment where pupils know it is acceptable to
  make mistakes when refereeing Reward referees when they handle challenges made towards
  their decision making. Ensure pupils are respecting one another's decisions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138886Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-perform-relay-changeovers-receiver
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often perform relay changeovers with the receiver standing still until
  they receive the baton, then accelerating into their sprint."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Changeovers should be performed at high speed. The receiver begins to
  accelerate at just the right moment to high speed but not too far ahead of the incoming
  runner. This will be different for each pupil (~3.5m is a good point to work from)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138891Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-longer-your-stride
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe that the longer your stride, the faster you'll run."@en ;
  curric:correction """Thinking about stride length and experimenting with different lengths can
  help pupils to understand the optimal length of stride and its relationship with cadence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139515Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-compare-their-progress-other
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may compare their progress to other pupils and feel disappointed if
  others have made a faster rate of progress."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Progress is personal and depends on many things - starting fitness, goals,
  technique and even how well rested you are on test day. Even small amounts of progress
  should be celebrated."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139521Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-audience-directly-facing-stage-performers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The audience are always directly facing the stage/performers."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst most theatres use an 'end on' arrangement, this isn't always the case.
  Fashion shows traditionally use a 'thrust' stage, lecture-demonstrations might use 'in the
  round' and performances such as Mummers' plays, may use 'promenade'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139526Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-body-adaptations-occur
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that body adaptations will occur and stay from training only
  once."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Body adaptations like stronger muscles or better endurance don’t happen after
  just one training session. To see improvements, you need to train regularly. If you stop
  training, your body can start to lose those gains – this is called reversibility."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139535Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-take-3-steps
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that to take 3 steps with the ball, you have to be dribbling."@en ;
  curric:correction """You only need to dribble if you want to take more than 3 steps. Once you
  catch the ball, you're allowed 3 steps without dribbling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139543Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-blaming-others-mistakes-rushing-rather
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Blaming others for mistakes and rushing rather than planning first and taking
  care over the approach."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Less overall time is lost if you invest in planning, negotiating and caring
  for each other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140014Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-coordinate-their-take
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle to coordinate their take off on to the springboard. Pupils
  land on the springboard with their heels."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use a short run up to develop good take off technique focusing on 1 foot to 2
  feet on the springboard. Pupils should always land on the balls of their feet to get more
  lift from the springboard."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140039Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-choose-obstacles-dont-link
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may choose obstacles that don't link well and therefore don't allow for
  smooth transitions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide lots of route planning support and examples/advice throughout the
  lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140834Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-upper-body-strength-primary-fitness
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Upper body strength is the primary fitness component required for seated
  volleyball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Core strength is fundamental to play seated volleyball effectively as it
  enables players to maintain their body position in the preparation and executon of skills
  throughout the game."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140840Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-working-bigger-groups-issues-group
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When working in bigger groups, there may be issues with group dynamics as
  pupils have to negotiate which movements they will use. Not all pupils in the group may be
  able to perform the movements."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could delegate a leader or be encouraged to listen to each other when
  working in bigger groups. Pupils may have to consider adapting their routines to help
  other members of their group."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-throw-stiff-arm-step
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often throw with a stiff arm and do not step into their pass with the
  opposite foot, resulting in inaccurate and unbalanced throws."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils can throw with the correct technique from a static
  position before adding any movement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141174Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-wicket-keeping-pupils-tendency-stand
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When wicket keeping, pupils have a tendency to stand right up to the wickets,
  no matter how fast the bowler is. This means they can't react quick enough to faster
  balls."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should understand that they can adjust the distance between wicket
  keeper and stumps, depending on the speed of the bowler, so they are catching the ball
  around thigh height. There is no standard wicket keeper position."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141388Z"^^xsd:dateTime .
